Gor Mahia will travel to England to face Everton in an eagerly anticipated friendly match at Goodison Park on either November 7 or 8. This was confirmed on Thursday by the two clubs and their sponsor, giant gaming firm SportPesa, who are the match organisers. “Marco Silva’s Everton side will welcome Kenyan SportPesa Premier League champions Gor Mahia FC at Goodison Park later this year following the African club’s victory in the SportPesa Super Cup final in June,” the English Premier League said in a statement. More to follow...  